Others: Massimo Luongo and Connor Metcalfe have been ruled out due to injuries.
Luke Brattan and Patrick Yazbek have been called up as replacements.
The Subway Socceroos will face China PR on October 10 at Adelaide Oval and Japan on October 15 at Saitama Stadium 2002.
The AFC Asian Qualifiers™ – Road to 26 will determine the teams qualifying for the FIFA World Cup 2026™.
Tickets for the match against China PR start from $15 Child, $20 Concession, $29 Adult, and $58 Family via Ticketek.
The match against China PR will be broadcast live on 10, 10 Play, and Paramount+.

The squad includes players such as Daniel Arzani, Keanu Baccus, Aziz Behich, Jordy Bos, Luke Brattan, Cameron Burgess, Thomas Deng, Mitchell Duke, Joe Gauci, Jason Geria, Craig Goodwin, Ajdin Hrustic, Nestor Irankunda, Jackson Irvine, Paul Izzo, Riley McGree, Lewis Miller, Aiden O’Neill, Kye Rowles, Mat Ryan, Sam Silvera, Harry Souttar, Apostolos Stamatelopoulos, Gianni Stensness, Nishan Velupillay, Patrick Yazbek, and Liam Young.
